      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Siding with AUTUMNHEAT (1) first up. He's off a decent spell here but his form last time in reads well for this level, fourth at Flemington, a BM66 winner at Geelong, second to the very progressive Straand Deal just some of the highlights. This trip is on the short side but he draws well and might just have a class edge. AMPHACTOR (5) has had three runs back and been solid enough in all, good at Geelong last time when third. He'll get a nice run and take catching. DEADLY PRESS (3) broke through for a narrow win at Seymour over a subsequent winner when last seen and has strong claims off that. KOMITO (6) ran well fresh at Bendigo and any natural improvement sees him hard to beat with the profile to say he can do so. SAVVIE BLANC (4) was just fair fresh but can improve onto turf.",
